## 2. Nayem Khan

**Profile:** LinkedIn — Fiverr freelancer and funnel optimizer
**Post Link:** https://www.linkedin.com/posts/nayemkhan_fiverr-salesfunnel-clientengagement-activity-7374563048474226688-ymlU

### What He Posted About

Nayem treats every buyer-seller interaction as a micro sales funnel. His post explains how optimizing the first response — the "query stage" — is where most conversions are won or lost. He shows how speed, social proof, and urgency at the first touchpoint convert small one-off gigs into long-term retainer clients.

His micro-funnel: Client query → Ultra-fast personalized reply → Trust building → Order → Upsell to bigger project

### What I Learned

Nayem's core insight is that **speed is a trust signal before any content is consumed.** A prospect who gets a reply in 2 minutes perceives the seller as professional and attentive. A prospect who waits 2 days has already started talking to someone else.

This maps directly to webinar funnels in a way most funnel builders miss. The confirmation email sent after registration is the "query stage reply" of a webinar funnel. If it arrives in seconds and feels personal — mentioning their name, what they will learn, and why it matters — show-up rates go up. If it is a generic automated blast that arrives 10 minutes later, they have already forgotten they registered.

**Applied to 100Hires:** The n8n webhook triggering a confirmation email within seconds of registration is not a nice-to-have — it is a conversion mechanism. Nayem's research backs this up with real before-and-after data from his own client work.

