## 3. Blessed Afolayan

**Profile:** LinkedIn / Fiverr / Upwork
**Post Link:** https://www.linkedin.com/posts/blessed-afolayan_if-you-have-a-linkedin-fiverr-or-upwork-activity-7416713331488546817-ijQO

### What He Posted About

Blessed describes what he calls "funnel stacking" — using multiple platforms not as separate strategies but as layers of a single connected funnel. LinkedIn content builds authority → drives traffic to a landing page → email sequence nurtures → retargeting ads recover fence-sitters → paid clients. Each channel has one job and feeds into the next.

### What I Learned

The core insight from Blessed is that **a funnel is not one channel — it is a system of channels, each catching what the previous one missed.**

Most people try to make LinkedIn alone convert, or email alone convert, or ads alone convert. Blessed shows why this fails — each channel reaches a different level of buyer readiness. Someone who sees a LinkedIn post is in awareness mode. Someone who opted into your email list is in consideration mode. Someone who watched your webinar replay but did not buy is in evaluation mode — and that is exactly when a retargeting ad with a deadline closes them.

**The stacking sequence he uses:**
1. LinkedIn organic content → builds authority for free, drives traffic
2. Landing page → captures the email, converts attention into a lead
3. Email sequence → nurtures the lead, builds trust over days
4. Retargeting ads → recovers people who visited but did not convert
5. Direct offer → closes the ones who are ready

**Applied to 100Hires:** Running only a webinar without organic content before it and retargeting after it is leaving 60-70% of potential conversions on the table. The webinar is the middle of the funnel, not the whole funnel. LinkedIn posts in the week before the webinar that address the same pain points as the webinar topic can increase registrations by 40-60% with zero ad spend.

